12void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::Run() {
13 LoopFinder loop_finder(phase_zone_, &graph_);
14 AnalyzerIterator iterator(phase_zone_, graph_, loop_finder);
15 while (iterator.HasNext()) {
16 const Block& block = *iterator.Next();
17 ProcessBlock(block);
18
19 // Finish snapshot.
20 Snapshot snapshot = types_table_.Seal();
21 block_to_snapshot_[block.index()] = MaybeSnapshot(snapshot);
22
23 // Consider re-processing for loops.
24 if (const GotoOp* last = block.LastOperation(graph_).TryCast<GotoOp>()) {
25 if (IsReachable(block) && last->destination->IsLoop() &&
26 last->destination->LastPredecessor() == &block) {
27 const Block& loop_header = *last->destination;
28 // Create a merged snapshot state for the forward- and backedge and
29 // process all operations inside the loop header.
30 ProcessBlock(loop_header);
31 Snapshot old_snapshot = block_to_snapshot_[loop_header.index()].value();
32 Snapshot snapshot = types_table_.Seal();
33 // TODO(14108): The snapshot isn't needed at all, we only care about the
34 // information if two snapshots are equivalent. Unfortunately, currently
35 // this can only be answered by creating a merge snapshot.
36 bool needs_revisit =
37 CreateMergeSnapshot(base::VectorOf({old_snapshot, snapshot}),
38 base::VectorOf({true, true}));
39 types_table_.Seal(); // Discard the snapshot.
40
41 // TODO(14108): This currently encodes a fixed point analysis where the
42 // analysis is finished once the backedge doesn't provide updated type
43 // information any more compared to the previous iteration. This could
44 // be stopped in cases where the backedge only refines types (i.e. only
45 // defines more precise types than the previous iteration).
46 if (needs_revisit) {
47 block_to_snapshot_[loop_header.index()] = MaybeSnapshot(snapshot);
48 // This will push the successors of the loop header to the iterator
49 // stack, so the loop body will be visited in the next iteration.
50 iterator.MarkLoopForRevisitSkipHeader();
51 }
52 }
53 }
54 }
55}
56
57void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessBlock(const Block& block) {
58 DCHECK_NULL(current_block_);
59 current_block_ = &block;
60 StartNewSnapshotFor(block);
61 ProcessOperations(block);
62 current_block_ = nullptr;
63}
64
65void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::StartNewSnapshotFor(const Block& block) {
66 is_first_loop_header_evaluation_ = false;
67 // Reset reachability information. This can be outdated in case of loop
68 // revisits. Below the reachability is calculated again and potentially
69 // re-added.
70 bool block_was_previously_reachable = IsReachable(block);
71 block_is_unreachable_.Remove(block.index().id());
72 // Start new snapshot based on predecessor information.
73 if (block.HasPredecessors() == 0) {
74 // The first block just starts with an empty snapshot.
75 DCHECK_EQ(block.index().id(), 0);
76 types_table_.StartNewSnapshot();
77 } else if (block.IsLoop()) {
78 const Block& forward_predecessor =
79 *block.LastPredecessor()->NeighboringPredecessor();
80 if (!IsReachable(forward_predecessor)) {
81 // If a loop isn't reachable through its forward edge, it can't possibly
82 // become reachable via the backedge.
83 block_is_unreachable_.Add(block.index().id());
84 }
85 MaybeSnapshot back_edge_snap =
86 block_to_snapshot_[block.LastPredecessor()->index()];
87 if (back_edge_snap.has_value() && block_was_previously_reachable) {
88 // The loop was already visited at least once. In this case use the
89 // available information from the backedge.
90 // Note that we only do this if the loop wasn't marked as unreachable
91 // before. This solves an issue where a single block loop would think the
92 // backedge is reachable as we just removed the unreachable information
93 // above. Once the analyzer hits the backedge, it will re-evaluate if the
94 // backedge changes any analysis results and then potentially revisit
95 // this loop with forward edge and backedge.
96 CreateMergeSnapshot(block);
97 } else {
98 // The loop wasn't visited yet. There isn't any type information available
99 // for the backedge.
100 is_first_loop_header_evaluation_ = true;
101 Snapshot forward_edge_snap =
102 block_to_snapshot_[forward_predecessor.index()].value();
103 types_table_.StartNewSnapshot(forward_edge_snap);
104 }
105 } else if (block.IsBranchTarget()) {
106 DCHECK_EQ(block.PredecessorCount(), 1);
107 const Block& predecessor = *block.LastPredecessor();
108 types_table_.StartNewSnapshot(
109 block_to_snapshot_[predecessor.index()].value());
110 if (IsReachable(predecessor)) {
111 const BranchOp* branch =
112 block.Predecessors()[0]->LastOperation(graph_).TryCast<BranchOp>();
113 if (branch != nullptr) {
114 ProcessBranchOnTarget(*branch, block);
115 }
116 } else {
117 block_is_unreachable_.Add(block.index().id());
118 }
119 } else {
120 DCHECK_EQ(block.kind(), Block::Kind::kMerge);
121 CreateMergeSnapshot(block);
122 }
123}
124
125void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessOperations(const Block& block) {
126 for (OpIndex op_idx : graph_.OperationIndices(block)) {
127 Operation& op = graph_.Get(op_idx);
128 switch (op.opcode) {
129 case Opcode::kWasmTypeCast:
130 ProcessTypeCast(op.Cast<WasmTypeCastOp>());
131 break;
132 case Opcode::kWasmTypeCheck:
133 ProcessTypeCheck(op.Cast<WasmTypeCheckOp>());
134 break;
135 case Opcode::kAssertNotNull:
136 ProcessAssertNotNull(op.Cast<AssertNotNullOp>());
137 break;
138 case Opcode::kNull:
139 ProcessNull(op.Cast<NullOp>());
140 break;
141 case Opcode::kIsNull:
142 ProcessIsNull(op.Cast<IsNullOp>());
143 break;
144 case Opcode::kParameter:
145 ProcessParameter(op.Cast<ParameterOp>());
146 break;
147 case Opcode::kStructGet:
148 ProcessStructGet(op.Cast<StructGetOp>());
149 break;
150 case Opcode::kStructSet:
151 ProcessStructSet(op.Cast<StructSetOp>());
152 break;
153 case Opcode::kArrayLength:
154 ProcessArrayLength(op.Cast<ArrayLengthOp>());
155 break;
156 case Opcode::kGlobalGet:
157 ProcessGlobalGet(op.Cast<GlobalGetOp>());
158 break;
159 case Opcode::kWasmRefFunc:
160 ProcessRefFunc(op.Cast<WasmRefFuncOp>());
161 break;
162 case Opcode::kWasmAllocateArray:
163 ProcessAllocateArray(op.Cast<WasmAllocateArrayOp>());
164 break;
165 case Opcode::kWasmAllocateStruct:
166 ProcessAllocateStruct(op.Cast<WasmAllocateStructOp>());
167 break;
168 case Opcode::kPhi:
169 ProcessPhi(op.Cast<PhiOp>());
170 break;
171 case Opcode::kWasmTypeAnnotation:
172 ProcessTypeAnnotation(op.Cast<WasmTypeAnnotationOp>());
173 break;
174 case Opcode::kBranch:
175 // Handling branch conditions implying special values is handled on the
176 // beginning of the successor block.
177 default:
178 break;
179 }
180 }
181}

183void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessTypeCast(const WasmTypeCastOp& type_cast) {
184 V<Object> object = type_cast.object();
185 wasm::ValueType target_type = type_cast.config.to;
186 wasm::ValueType known_input_type = RefineTypeKnowledge(object, target_type);
187 input_type_map_[graph_.Index(type_cast)] = known_input_type;
188}
189
190void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessTypeCheck(const WasmTypeCheckOp& type_check) {
191 wasm::ValueType type = GetResolvedType(type_check.object());
192 input_type_map_[graph_.Index(type_check)] = type;
193}
194
195void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessAssertNotNull(
196 const AssertNotNullOp& assert_not_null) {
197 V<Object> object = assert_not_null.object();
198 wasm::ValueType new_type = assert_not_null.type.AsNonNull();
199 wasm::ValueType known_input_type = RefineTypeKnowledge(object, new_type);
200 input_type_map_[graph_.Index(assert_not_null)] = known_input_type;
201}
202
203void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessIsNull(const IsNullOp& is_null) {
204 input_type_map_[graph_.Index(is_null)] = GetResolvedType(is_null.object());
205}

207void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessParameter(const ParameterOp& parameter) {
208 if (parameter.parameter_index != wasm::kWasmInstanceParameterIndex) {
209 RefineTypeKnowledge(graph_.Index(parameter),
210 signature_->GetParam(parameter.parameter_index - 1));
211 }
212}

214void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessStructGet(const StructGetOp& struct_get) {
215 // struct.get performs a null check.
216 wasm::ValueType type = RefineTypeKnowledgeNotNull(struct_get.object());
217 input_type_map_[graph_.Index(struct_get)] = type;
218 RefineTypeKnowledge(graph_.Index(struct_get),
219 struct_get.type->field(struct_get.field_index));
220}
221
222void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessStructSet(const StructSetOp& struct_set) {
223 // struct.set performs a null check.
224 wasm::ValueType type = RefineTypeKnowledgeNotNull(struct_set.object());
225 input_type_map_[graph_.Index(struct_set)] = type;
226}
227
228void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessArrayLength(const ArrayLengthOp& array_length) {
229 // array.len performs a null check.
230 wasm::ValueType type = RefineTypeKnowledgeNotNull(array_length.array());
231 input_type_map_[graph_.Index(array_length)] = type;
232}

234void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessGlobalGet(const GlobalGetOp& global_get) {
235 RefineTypeKnowledge(graph_.Index(global_get), global_get.global->type);
236}

238void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessRefFunc(const WasmRefFuncOp& ref_func) {
239 uint32_t sig_index = module_->functions[ref_func.function_index].sig_index;
240 RefineTypeKnowledge(graph_.Index(ref_func), wasm::ValueType::Ref(sig_index));

259void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessPhi(const PhiOp& phi) {
260 // The result type of a phi is the union of all its input types.
261 // If any of the inputs is the default value ValueType(), there isn't any type
262 // knowledge inferrable.
263 DCHECK_GT(phi.input_count, 0);
264 if (is_first_loop_header_evaluation_) {
265 // We don't know anything about the backedge yet, so we only use the
266 // forward edge. We will revisit the loop header again once the block with
267 // the back edge is evaluated.
268 RefineTypeKnowledge(graph_.Index(phi), GetResolvedType((phi.input(0))));
269 return;
270 }
271 wasm::ValueType union_type =
272 types_table_.GetPredecessorValue(ResolveAliases(phi.input(0)), 0);
273 if (union_type == wasm::ValueType()) return;
274 for (int i = 1; i < phi.input_count; ++i) {
275 wasm::ValueType input_type =
276 types_table_.GetPredecessorValue(ResolveAliases(phi.input(i)), i);
277 if (input_type == wasm::ValueType()) return;
278 // <bottom> types have to be skipped as an unreachable predecessor doesn't
279 // change our type knowledge.
280 // TODO(mliedtke): Ideally, we'd skip unreachable predecessors here
281 // completely, as we might loosen the known type due to an unreachable
282 // predecessor.
283 if (input_type.is_uninhabited()) continue;
284 if (union_type.is_uninhabited()) {
285 union_type = input_type;
286 } else {
287 union_type = wasm::Union(union_type, input_type, module_, module_).type;
288 }
289 }
290 RefineTypeKnowledge(graph_.Index(phi), union_type);
291}

293void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessTypeAnnotation(
294 const WasmTypeAnnotationOp& type_annotation) {
295 RefineTypeKnowledge(type_annotation.value(), type_annotation.type);
296}

298void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessBranchOnTarget(const BranchOp& branch,
299 const Block& target) {
300 DCHECK_EQ(current_block_, &target);
301 const Operation& condition = graph_.Get(branch.condition());
302 switch (condition.opcode) {
303 case Opcode::kWasmTypeCheck: {
304 const WasmTypeCheckOp& check = condition.Cast<WasmTypeCheckOp>();
305 if (branch.if_true == &target) {
306 // It is known from now on that the type is at least the checked one.
307 RefineTypeKnowledge(check.object(), check.config.to);
308 } else {
309 DCHECK_EQ(branch.if_false, &target);
310 if (wasm::IsSubtypeOf(GetResolvedType(check.object()), check.config.to,
311 module_)) {
312 // The type check always succeeds, the target is impossible to be
313 // reached.
314 DCHECK_EQ(target.PredecessorCount(), 1);
315 block_is_unreachable_.Add(target.index().id());
316 }
317 }
318 } break;
319 case Opcode::kIsNull: {
320 const IsNullOp& is_null = condition.Cast<IsNullOp>();
321 if (branch.if_true == &target) {
322 if (GetResolvedType(is_null.object()).is_non_nullable()) {
323 // The target is impossible to be reached.
324 DCHECK_EQ(target.PredecessorCount(), 1);
325 block_is_unreachable_.Add(target.index().id());
326 return;
327 }
328 RefineTypeKnowledge(is_null.object(),
329 wasm::ToNullSentinel({is_null.type, module_}));
330 } else {
331 DCHECK_EQ(branch.if_false, &target);
332 RefineTypeKnowledge(is_null.object(), is_null.type.AsNonNull());
333 }
334 } break;
335 default:
336 break;
337 }
338}
339
340void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ProcessNull(const NullOp& null) {
341 wasm::ValueType null_type = wasm::ToNullSentinel({null.type, module_});
342 RefineTypeKnowledge(graph_.Index(null), null_type);
343}

345void WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::CreateMergeSnapshot(const Block& block) {
346 base::SmallVector<Snapshot, 8> snapshots;
347 // Unreachable predecessors should be ignored when merging but we can't remove
348 // them from the predecessors as that would mess up the phi inputs. Therefore
349 // the reachability of the predecessors is passed as a separate list.
350 base::SmallVector<bool, 8> reachable;
351 bool all_predecessors_unreachable = true;
352 for (const Block* predecessor : block.PredecessorsIterable()) {
353 snapshots.push_back(block_to_snapshot_[predecessor->index()].value());
354 bool predecessor_reachable = IsReachable(*predecessor);
355 reachable.push_back(predecessor_reachable);
356 all_predecessors_unreachable &= !predecessor_reachable;
357 }
358 if (all_predecessors_unreachable) {
359 block_is_unreachable_.Add(block.index().id());
360 }
361 // The predecessor snapshots need to be reversed to restore the "original"
362 // order of predecessors. (This is used to map phi inputs to their
363 // corresponding predecessor.)
364 std::reverse(snapshots.begin(), snapshots.end());
365 std::reverse(reachable.begin(), reachable.end());
366 CreateMergeSnapshot(base::VectorOf(snapshots), base::VectorOf(reachable));
367}
368
369bool WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::CreateMergeSnapshot(
370 base::Vector<const Snapshot> predecessors,
371 base::Vector<const bool> reachable) {
372 DCHECK_EQ(predecessors.size(), reachable.size());
373 // The merging logic is also used to evaluate if two snapshots are
374 // "identical", i.e. the known types for all operations are the same.
375 bool types_are_equivalent = true;
376 types_table_.StartNewSnapshot(
377 predecessors, [this, &types_are_equivalent, reachable](
378 TypeSnapshotTable::Key,
379 base::Vector<const wasm::ValueType> predecessors) {
380 DCHECK_GT(predecessors.size(), 1);
381 size_t i = 0;
382 // Initialize the type based on the first reachable predecessor.
383 wasm::ValueType first = wasm::kWasmBottom;
384 for (; i < reachable.size(); ++i) {
385 // Uninhabitated types can only occur in unreachable code e.g. as a
386 // result of an always failing cast. Still reachability tracking might
387 // in some cases miss that a block becomes unreachable, so we still
388 // check for uninhabited in the if below.
389 DCHECK_IMPLIES(reachable[i], !predecessors[i].is_uninhabited());
390 if (reachable[i] && !predecessors[i].is_uninhabited()) {
391 first = predecessors[i];
392 ++i;
393 break;
394 }
395 }
396
397 wasm::ValueType res = first;
398 for (; i < reachable.size(); ++i) {
399 if (!reachable[i]) continue; // Skip unreachable predecessors.
400 wasm::ValueType type = predecessors[i];
401 // Uninhabitated types can only occur in unreachable code e.g. as a
402 // result of an always failing cast. Still reachability tracking might
403 // in some cases miss that a block becomes unreachable, so we still
404 // check for uninhabited in the if below.
405 DCHECK(!type.is_uninhabited());
406 if (type.is_uninhabited()) continue;
407 types_are_equivalent &= first == type;
408 if (res == wasm::ValueType() || type == wasm::ValueType()) {
409 res = wasm::ValueType();
410 } else {
411 res = wasm::Union(res, type, module_, module_).type;
412 }
413 }
414 return res;
415 });
416 return !types_are_equivalent;
417}
418
419wasm::ValueType WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::RefineTypeKnowledge(
420 OpIndex object, wasm::ValueType new_type) {
421 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current_block_);
422 object = ResolveAliases(object);
423 wasm::ValueType previous_value = types_table_.Get(object);
424 wasm::ValueType intersection_type =
425 previous_value == wasm::ValueType()
426 ? new_type
427 : wasm::Intersection(previous_value, new_type, module_, module_).type;
428 if (intersection_type.is_uninhabited()) {
429 block_is_unreachable_.Add(current_block_->index().id());
430 }
431 types_table_.Set(object, intersection_type);
432 return previous_value;
433}
434
435wasm::ValueType WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::RefineTypeKnowledgeNotNull(OpIndex object) {
436 object = ResolveAliases(object);
437 wasm::ValueType previous_value = types_table_.Get(object);
438 wasm::ValueType not_null_type = previous_value.AsNonNull();
439 if (not_null_type.is_uninhabited()) {
440 block_is_unreachable_.Add(current_block_->index().id());
441 }
442 types_table_.Set(object, not_null_type);
443 return previous_value;
444}
445
446OpIndex WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::ResolveAliases(OpIndex object) const {
447 while (true) {
448 const Operation* op = &graph_.Get(object);
449 switch (op->opcode) {
450 case Opcode::kWasmTypeCast:
451 object = op->Cast<WasmTypeCastOp>().object();
452 break;
453 case Opcode::kAssertNotNull:
454 object = op->Cast<AssertNotNullOp>().object();
455 break;
456 case Opcode::kWasmTypeAnnotation:
457 object = op->Cast<WasmTypeAnnotationOp>().value();
458 break;
459 default:
460 return object;
461 }
462 }
463}
464
465bool WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::IsReachable(const Block& block) const {
466 return !block_is_unreachable_.Contains(block.index().id());
467}
468
469wasm::ValueType WasmGCTypeAnalyzer::GetResolvedType(OpIndex object) const {
470 return types_table_.Get(ResolveAliases(object));
471}
